Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity
O(n × m)

Where:

n = number of strings
m = length of the longest string

In the worst case, the prefix may be shortened multiple times for every string.

Space Complexity
O(1)

Only a few variables are used.

Key Takeaway

The core idea is:

Start with the first string as the prefix.
If another string doesn't start with it,
keep removing characters from the end
until it becomes a valid prefix.
